		<div class="qna-section">
			<div class="question">Question 2: How to prepare for the companies of that sector.</div>

			<div class="answer">Answer:
			<ol style="margin-left:20px">
			<ul style="margin-left:20px">
			<li>I am in the robotics software team, so for that you need:-
			<ol style="margin-left:20px;">
			<li>Good Programming (C++/Python) </li>
			<li>Good theoretical knowledge of ROS (Robot Operating System) </li>
			<li>Basic understanding of Linux. </li>
			</ol>
			</li>

			<li>The level of programming skills should be equivalent to the skill of any candidate getting selected in an IT firm and this is also the most fundamental thing. </li>

			<li>Apart from that the projects that highlight your robotics skills also improve your chances of getting into one of these firms. </li>

			<li>Any research paper, hackathon, achievement in similar field will definitely boost your profile. </li>

			<li>So to summarise there is not a fixed path to enter into this field and that is the beauty, you get to experiment with a lot of things and then filter out things you like.</li>

			<li>But consistency is one thing that is important. It's obviously not a 5-6 months process that will guarantee you the selection like it is with most of the fields it is the whole 3.5 - 4 years of constant effort and hard work that will give you the result. </li>

			<li>If you want to stand apart from the crowd, your efforts have to be extraordinary.</li>

			</ul>
			</div>
