		<div class="qna-section">
			<div class="question">Question 3: Describe the selection procedure of that company.</div>

				<div class="answer">Answer: 
			So this was an off-campus process.
			I applied through LinkedIn. 

			<ol style="margin-left:20px"><li>The first round was a 2hr screening test. 
			Which was not your typical coding round. 
			It was a mix of both coding and your ability to understand the code structure. The code was spread across various files with various classes, so it also tested your OOPS concept at the same time. </li>

			<li>The second round was a 1.5 hr video-interview process. So it was a typical interview wherein the interviewer questioned me on technical concepts, situational conditions and on some of my projects. </li>

			<li>The third round was again basically a 1 hr coding round. 

			And so this was the final round after which I was selected for the role. </li></ol>

			</div>
