		<div class="qna-section" style="padding-bottom:20px;">
			<div class="question">Question 7:Any extra advice to your juniors for technical skills that they should develop?</div>

			<div class="answer">Answer: 
			It's very important to constantly introspect yourself. Only you know the skill you are not comfortable with and if it interests you, then you should definitely improve that.

			It's worse to have a shallow understanding of a topic than to not know it all. Because when asked questions it will appear that you are guessing the answer which will leave a very negative impression of your personality. 

			So my way was to write all the skills I want to improve in some order and try to read the documentation available whenever possible. Because you will encounter various topics so it's important to keep track of those that interest you. 
